Package com.intellij.openapi.externalSystem.service.settings

Class AbstractExternalProjectSettingsControl<S extends ExternalProjectSettings>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.openapi.externalSystem.service.settings.AbstractSettingsControl
      • com.intellij.openapi.externalSystem.service.settings.AbstractExternalProjectSettingsControl<S>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExternalSystemSettingsControl<S>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GradleProjectSettingsControl

    public abstract class AbstractExternalProjectSettingsControl<S extends ExternalProjectSettings>
extends AbstractSettingsControl
implements ExternalSystemSettingsControl<S>
    Templates class for managing single external project settings (single ide project might contain multiple bindings to external projects, e.g. one module is backed by a single external project and couple of others are backed by a single external multi-project).

      • fillUi

        public void fillUi(PaintAwarePanel canvas,
                   int indentLevel)
        Description copied from interface: ExternalSystemSettingsControl
        Adds current control-specific UI controls to the given canvas.

        Note: given canvas component is expected to be managed by a GridBagLayout. That is the reason on why we use this method instead of a method like 'JComponent getComponent()' - there is a possible case that given canvas has components from more than one control and we might want them to be aligned.

        Specified by:
        fillUi in interface ExternalSystemSettingsControl<S extends ExternalProjectSettings>
        Parameters:
        canvas - container to use as a holder for UI components specific to the current control
        indentLevel - a hint on how much UI components added by the current control should be indented
